def  box_plot(df):
  cat_columns = []
  for i in df.columns:
    if (((df[i].dtype.name) == 'float64') ):
      cat_columns.append(i)
  ncols = 3
  nrows = len(cat_columns) // ncols + (len(cat_columns) % ncols > 0)
  plt.figure(figsize=(30,30))
  for i, j in enumerate(cat_columns):
    plt.subplot(nrows, ncols, i+1)
    ax=sns.boxplot(df[j],color='blue')
    ax.set_title("boxplot of "+j)
  return plt.show()

In [14]:
for i in df_signal.columns:
    if (((df_signal[i].dtype.name) == 'float64') ):
      Q1=df_signal[i].quantile(0.25)
      Q3=df_signal[i].quantile(0.75)
      IQR=Q3-Q1
      lower = Q1 - 1.5*IQR
      upper = Q3 + 1.5*IQR
      median = df_signal[i].median()
      df_signal[i][df_signal[i] < lower] = median
      df_signal[i][df_signal[i] > upper] = median

def single_layer(output_nodes):

  model = Sequential()
  model.add(Dense(256, activation='relu',kernel_initializer='he_uniform',input_dim = X_train.shape[1] ))
  model.add(Dense(output_nodes, activation='softmax'))
  #compile mode-
  adam = optimizers.Adam(learning_rate=1e-3)
  model.compile(loss=losses.categorical_crossentropy, optimizer=adam, metrics=['accuracy'])
  return model

checkpoint = ModelCheckpoint("model.weights.h5",monitor='val_accuracy',
                            save_weights_only=True, mode='max',verbose=0)
reduce_lr = ReduceLROnPlateau(monitor='val_loss',factor=0.1,patience=2,min_lr=0.001,model='auto')
callbacks = [checkpoint,reduce_lr]
model= single_layer(output_nodes)
print(model.summary())

def multilayer_sigmoids_sgd(output_nodes):
  model = Sequential()
  model.add(Dense(50, input_dim = X_train.shape[1]))
  model.add(Activation('sigmoid'))
  model.add(Dense(50))
  model.add(Activation('sigmoid'))
  model.add(Dense(50))
  model.add(Activation('sigmoid'))
  model.add(Dense(50))
  model.add(Activation('sigmoid'))
  model.add(Dense(output_nodes))
  model.add(Activation('softmax'))
  sgd = optimizers.SGD(learning_rate = learning_rate)
  model.compile(optimizer = sgd, loss = 'categorical_crossentropy', metrics = ['accuracy'])
  return model

def multilayer_relu_dropouts_adam(output_nodes):
  model = Sequential()
  model.add(Dense(256,activation='relu',input_dim = X_train.shape[1]))
  model.add(Dropout(0.2))
  model.add(Dense(128,activation='relu'))
  model.add(Dropout(0.2))
  model.add(Dense(64,activation='relu'))
  model.add(Dropout(0.2))
  model.add(Dense(32,activation='relu'))
  model.add(Dense(output_nodes, activation = 'softmax'))
  optimizer = optimizers.Adam(learning_rate)
  model.compile(loss='categorical_crossentropy',optimizer=optimizer,metrics=['accuracy'])
  return model

model= multilayer_relu_dropouts_adam(output_nodes)

def complicated_model(output_nodes):
    model = Sequential()
    model.add(Dense(50, input_dim = X_train.shape[1], kernel_initializer='he_normal'))
    model.add(BatchNormalization())
    model.add(Activation('relu'))
    model.add(Dropout(0.2))
    model.add(Dense(50, kernel_initializer='he_normal'))
    model.add(BatchNormalization())
    model.add(Activation('relu'))
    model.add(Dropout(0.2))
    model.add(Dense(50, kernel_initializer='he_normal'))
    model.add(BatchNormalization())
    model.add(Activation('relu'))
    model.add(Dropout(0.2))
    model.add(Dense(50, kernel_initializer='he_normal'))
    model.add(BatchNormalization())
    model.add(Activation('relu'))
    model.add(Dropout(0.2))
    model.add(Dense(output_nodes, kernel_initializer='he_normal'))
    model.add(Activation('softmax'))
    adam = optimizers.Adam(learning_rate = learning_rate)
    model.compile(optimizer = adam, loss = 'categorical_crossentropy', metrics = ['accuracy'])
    return model

from tensorflow.keras.models import Sequential
from tensorflow.keras.layers import Dense, LeakyReLU

epochs=100
def lekyRelu_fun(output_nodes):
    model = Sequential()
    model.add(Dense(128, kernel_initializer='normal', input_dim=X_train.shape[1], activation='sigmoid'))
    model.add(Dense(64, kernel_initializer='normal', activation='sigmoid'))
    model.add(Dense(32, kernel_initializer='normal'))
    model.add(LeakyReLU(alpha=0.1))
    model.add(Dense(16, kernel_initializer='normal'))
    model.add(LeakyReLU(alpha=0.1))
    model.add(Dense(output_nodes, kernel_initializer='normal', activation='softmax'))
    model.compile(loss='categorical_crossentropy', optimizer='adam', metrics=['accuracy'])
    return model
In [40]:
dataset_analysis = pd.DataFrame(columns=['model_name','test_loss', 'test_accuracy', 'training loss', 'training accuracy','val loss', 'val accuracy'])
def table(model, NN, model_name):
    # Evaluate the model on the test set
    results = model.evaluate(X_test, y_test)
    test_loss=results[0]
    test_accuracy=results[1]

    # Calculate training accuracy and loss
    training_accuracy = np.mean(NN.history['accuracy'])
    training_loss = np.mean(NN.history['loss'])

    # Calculate validation accuracy and loss
    val_accuracy = np.mean(NN.history['val_accuracy'])
    val_loss = np.mean(NN.history['val_loss'])

    # Add a new row to the DataFrame
    global dataset_analysis
    dataset_analysis = dataset_analysis.append({'model_name':model_name,
                                                'test_loss': test_loss,
                                                'test_accuracy': test_accuracy,
                                                'training loss': training_loss,
                                                'training accuracy': training_accuracy,
                                                'val loss': val_loss,
                                                'val accuracy': val_accuracy
                                                                  },
                                               ignore_index=True)

In [45]:
balanced_dataset_analysis = pd.DataFrame(columns=['model_name','test_loss', 'test_accuracy', 'training loss', 'training accuracy', 'val loss', 'val accuracy'])

def table2(model, NN, model_name):
    # Evaluate the model on the test set
    results = model.evaluate(X_test, y_test)
    test_loss=results[0]
    test_accuracy=results[1]

    # Calculate training accuracy and loss
    training_accuracy = np.mean(NN.history['accuracy'])
    training_loss = np.mean(NN.history['loss'])

    # Calculate validation accuracy and loss
    val_accuracy = np.mean(NN.history['val_accuracy'])
    val_loss = np.mean(NN.history['val_loss'])

    # Add a new row to the DataFrame
    global balanced_dataset_analysis
    balanced_dataset_analysis = balanced_dataset_analysis.append({'model_name':model_name,
                                                'test_loss': test_loss,
                                                'test_accuracy': test_accuracy,
                                                'training loss': training_loss,
                                                'training accuracy': training_accuracy,
                                                'val loss': val_loss,
                                                'val accuracy': val_accuracy
                                                                  },
                                               ignore_index=True)

def single_layer(output_nodes):

  model = Sequential()
  model.add(Dense(256, activation='sigmoid',kernel_initializer='he_uniform',input_dim = X_train.shape[1] ))
  model.add(Dense(output_nodes, activation='softmax'))
  #compile mode-
  adam = optimizers.Adam(learning_rate=1e-3)
  model.compile(loss=losses.categorical_crossentropy, optimizer=adam, metrics=['accuracy'])
  return model

checkpoint = ModelCheckpoint("model.weights.h5",monitor='accuracy',
                            save_weights_only=True, mode='max',verbose=0)
reduce_lr = ReduceLROnPlateau(monitor='accuracy',factor=0.1,patience=2,min_lr=0.001,model='auto')
callbacks = [checkpoint,reduce_lr]
model= single_layer(output_nodes)
print(model.summary())

def multilayer_sigmoids_sgd(output_nodes):
  model = Sequential()
  model.add(Dense(50, input_dim = X_train.shape[1]))
  model.add(Activation('sigmoid'))
  model.add(Dense(50))
  model.add(Activation('sigmoid'))
  model.add(Dense(50))
  model.add(Activation('sigmoid'))
  model.add(Dense(50))
  model.add(Activation('sigmoid'))
  model.add(Dense(output_nodes))
  model.add(Activation('softmax'))
  sgd = optimizers.SGD(learning_rate = learning_rate)
  model.compile(optimizer = sgd, loss = 'categorical_crossentropy', metrics = ['accuracy'])
  return model

def multilayer_relu_dropouts_adam(output_nodes):
  model = Sequential()
  model.add(Dense(256,activation='relu',input_dim = X_train.shape[1]))
  model.add(Dropout(0.2))
  model.add(Dense(128,activation='relu'))
  model.add(Dropout(0.2))
  model.add(Dense(64,activation='relu'))
  model.add(Dropout(0.2))
  model.add(Dense(32,activation='relu'))
  model.add(Dense(output_nodes, activation = 'softmax'))
  optimizer = optimizers.Adam(learning_rate)
  model.compile(loss='categorical_crossentropy',optimizer=optimizer,metrics=['accuracy'])
  return model

def complicated_model(output_nodes):
    model = Sequential()
    model.add(Dense(50, input_dim = X_train.shape[1], kernel_initializer='he_normal'))
    model.add(BatchNormalization())
    model.add(Activation('relu'))
    model.add(Dropout(0.2))
    model.add(Dense(50, kernel_initializer='he_normal'))
    model.add(BatchNormalization())
    model.add(Activation('relu'))
    model.add(Dropout(0.2))
    model.add(Dense(50, kernel_initializer='he_normal'))
    model.add(BatchNormalization())
    model.add(Activation('relu'))
    model.add(Dropout(0.2))
    model.add(Dense(50, kernel_initializer='he_normal'))
    model.add(BatchNormalization())
    model.add(Activation('relu'))
    model.add(Dropout(0.2))
    model.add(Dense(output_nodes, kernel_initializer='he_normal'))
    model.add(Activation('softmax'))
    adam = optimizers.Adam(learning_rate = learning_rate)
    model.compile(optimizer = adam, loss = 'categorical_crossentropy', metrics = ['accuracy'])
    return model
In [70]:
dataset_analysis = pd.DataFrame(columns=['model_name','test_loss', 'test_accuracy', 'training loss', 'training accuracy','val loss', 'val accuracy'])
def table(model, NN, model_name):
    # Evaluate the model on the test set
    results = model.evaluate(x_test, y_test_cat)
    test_loss=results[0]
    test_accuracy=results[1]

    # Calculate training accuracy and loss
    training_accuracy = np.mean(NN.history['accuracy'])
    training_loss = np.mean(NN.history['loss'])

    # Calculate validation accuracy and loss
    val_accuracy = np.mean(NN.history['val_accuracy'])
    val_loss = np.mean(NN.history['val_loss'])

    # Add a new row to the DataFrame
    global dataset_analysis
    dataset_analysis = dataset_analysis.append({'model_name':model_name,
                                                'test_loss': test_loss,
                                                'test_accuracy': test_accuracy,
                                                'training loss': training_loss,
                                                'training accuracy': training_accuracy,
                                                'val loss': val_loss,
                                                'val accuracy': val_accuracy
                                                                  },
                                               ignore_index=True)

from tensorflow.keras.models import Sequential
from tensorflow.keras.layers import Dense, LeakyReLU

epochs=100
def leakyRelu_fun(output_nodes):
    model = Sequential()
    model.add(Dense(128, kernel_initializer='normal', input_dim=X_train.shape[1], activation='relu'))
    model.add(Dense(64, kernel_initializer='normal', activation='relu'))
    model.add(Dense(32, kernel_initializer='normal'))
    model.add(LeakyReLU(alpha=0.1))
    model.add(Dense(16, kernel_initializer='normal'))
    model.add(LeakyReLU(alpha=0.1))
    model.add(Dense(output_nodes, kernel_initializer='normal', activation='softmax'))
    model.compile(loss='categorical_crossentropy', optimizer='adam', metrics=['accuracy'])
    return model
